-- Dabur India to Raise 20 Billion Rupees for Acquisitions, Standard Reports
-- Thomas Abraham
-- 2010-07-30T01:35:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-30/dabur-india-to-raise-20-billion-rupees-for-acquisitions-standard-reports.html

          
          
             Dabur India Ltd., which makes
products ranging from shampoos to beverages, plans to raise 20
billion rupees ($430 million) to fund acquisitions, the Business
Standard reported, citing company’s Chief Executive Officer
Sunil Duggal. The company’s board approved a resolution for the
fundraising two weeks ago, the newspaper said.  
